Oskar Fredrik Vilhelm Olaf Gustav Adolf Bernadotte av Sverige, King of Sweden, was born 11 November 1882 in Stockholm, Sweden to Gustaf V av Sverige (1858-1950) and Viktoria von Baden (1862-1930) and died 15 September 1973 Helsingborgs lasarett, Helsingborg, Sweden of unspecified causes. He married Margaret of Connaught (1882-1920) 15 June 1905 in St. George's Chapel, at Windsor Castle, Windsor, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom. He married Louise Mountbatten (1889-1965) 3 November 1923 in London, England, United Kingdom.
